title: Carroll's boys, girls champs at New Haven cross country semi-state
text:
Carroll's boys, girls champs at New Haven cross country semi-state 
By Dean Pantazi - 21 Alive October 24, 2015 Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 11:48 PM EDT 
FORT WAYNE, Ind. (21 Alive) - Carroll took both the boys and girls team titles on Saturday at the New Have cross country semi-states at the Plex. 
The Carroll boys won with 84 points, and will be joined by Concordia, Mt. Vernon, Westview, Northridge, and Pendleton Heights as the top six teams who advance to the state meet in Terre Haute next week. 
Digital Daily â€“ subscribe to our daily newsletter 
Christian Noble of Mt. Vernon was individual winner in 15:18.50. 
Carroll's girls won with 69 points to 85 for runnerup Pendleton Heights, and those two willbe joined by Homestead, Penn, Northridge, and Huntington North at state as teams. 
Alex Buck of Pendleton Heights won indiviidually in 17:57.14.
